09:29.277 --> 09:31.279
I threw up.

09:31.446 --> 09:33.699
Oh, it's okay, son.

09:39.871 --> 09:43.296
Where's Mum?

09:43.458 --> 09:46.052
She's, um...

09:46.211 --> 09:48.760
she'll be home in a minute.

09:59.265 --> 10:01.313
Door open, Dad.

10:04.938 --> 10:06.565
Yeah.

10:47.772 --> 10:49.570
Petra...

10:49.732 --> 10:52.906
can you hold
this for me...

10:53.069 --> 10:54.992
right up there
like that?

10:55.155 --> 10:56.702
Just like that?

10:56.865 --> 10:59.539
Okay, so the potato
peeler is used first.

10:59.701 --> 11:02.045
And that's these
superficial wounds here.

11:02.203 --> 11:03.500
That's why there's not

11:03.663 --> 11:06.212
a great amount
of blood.

11:06.374 --> 11:08.797
And the stabbing arc
is quite short.

11:08.960 --> 11:12.430
Then he picks up a knife
and he slashes,

11:12.589 --> 11:14.307
closer, downward.

11:14.465 --> 11:15.591
Like this.

11:15.758 --> 11:18.227
And finally, a cleaver.

11:18.386 --> 11:20.639
And that's what causes
the blood to spray.

11:20.805 --> 11:22.057
Right.

11:22.223 --> 11:24.021
Which is consistent
with the assailant

11:24.184 --> 11:26.107
sitting astride the man...

11:26.269 --> 11:27.816
and hacking...

11:27.979 --> 11:29.572
downwards and...

11:32.066 --> 11:33.864
What?

11:34.027 --> 11:35.199
I don't know.

11:35.361 --> 11:37.705
I can see something
strange, I think.

11:39.699 --> 11:41.918
There's something inside him,

11:42.076 --> 11:44.670
something tiny.

11:47.749 --> 11:50.093
What do you see?

11:50.251 --> 11:51.503
A foreign object.

11:51.669 --> 11:53.888
A fragment--
stuck to the lower left rib.

11:54.047 --> 11:55.890
The underside
of the rib.

11:56.049 --> 11:58.268
Can't see it.

12:00.386 --> 12:02.059
Would you pull it out, please?

12:12.899 --> 12:15.823
At first I thought
it was a bone fragment, but...

12:20.615 --> 12:23.585
It's a fingernail.

12:26.412 --> 12:28.289
From a child?

12:30.833 --> 12:33.712
Hyperbaric oxygen treatment
can help damaged cells recover.

12:33.878 --> 12:36.506
Any tissue in Liam's feet

12:36.673 --> 12:40.348
that can be saved will be
as long as he is in there.

12:40.510 --> 12:42.433
And what happens
if we wake him up?

12:42.595 --> 12:44.768
Just long enough
to speak to him?

12:44.931 --> 12:48.356
When he becomes fully
conscious, the pain will be

12:48.518 --> 12:50.612
unbearable.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.568
Well, then,
that's not an option.

12:52.730 --> 12:54.903
We could leave the child alone

12:55.066 --> 12:56.784
and learn nothing,

12:56.943 --> 12:59.822
or we can wake him up,
and we get some answers.

12:59.988 --> 13:03.367
I think we have
to wake him up.

13:05.285 --> 13:07.538
Yes.

13:07.704 --> 13:10.924
But not before
I talk to the mother.

13:11.082 --> 13:12.550
No. No!

13:12.709 --> 13:14.803
No.

13:14.961 --> 13:16.213
You listen to me.

13:16.379 --> 13:17.801
Someone must have
put that there.

13:17.964 --> 13:19.261
That is not him.

13:19.424 --> 13:20.471
I'm sorry, Jules.

13:20.633 --> 13:21.555
No!

13:25.555 --> 13:27.353
Don't touch me.
Come on.

13:27.515 --> 13:29.142
You-you get off me!

13:29.309 --> 13:32.529
Somebody’s
done this to him.

13:32.687 --> 13:35.440
Jules, look at me.

13:39.569 --> 13:42.413
Liam's going
to be okay.

13:42.572 --> 13:45.325
I won't let any harm
come to your son.

13:45.491 --> 13:48.711
You promised me that before.

13:48.870 --> 13:50.713
We have to wake him.

13:50.872 --> 13:53.000
No. Fuck you!

13:53.166 --> 13:54.509
Leave him alone!

13:54.667 --> 13:57.090
Fuck you!
Leave him alone!

13:57.253 --> 13:59.347
You leave him alone, Dan!

14:22.278 --> 14:24.201
Hey, sweetie.

14:24.364 --> 14:26.617
It's Mummy.

14:26.783 --> 14:29.036
Mummy's here.

14:30.370 --> 14:33.169
Are you awake?

14:35.291 --> 14:36.918
Liam?

14:37.085 --> 14:40.259
Rapid low-voltage EEG.

14:40.421 --> 14:42.423
He's beginning to wake now.

14:42.590 --> 14:46.811
I'm going to up his painkiller
by five mill.

14:46.969 --> 14:49.768
Liam, can you hear me?

14:51.099 --> 14:53.318
Mum?

14:53.476 --> 14:56.400
Hey. It's okay, sweetheart.

14:56.562 --> 14:59.486
You're safe, and the
doctor's looking after you.

14:59.649 --> 15:01.367
I want you to
talk to somebody,

15:01.526 --> 15:03.449
Okay?

15:03.611 --> 15:05.864
Answer the questions.

15:14.205 --> 15:16.503
Liam?

15:16.666 --> 15:20.387
How are you feeling?

15:20.545 --> 15:22.764
So, I'm gonna ask
you some questions.

15:22.922 --> 15:25.050
You think you
can follow me?

15:28.302 --> 15:29.770
Liam? I think he's drifting.

15:29.929 --> 15:31.306
Give it a moment.

15:31.472 --> 15:33.520
Be quick please.
I will. I will.

15:33.683 --> 15:35.777
Liam,

15:35.935 --> 15:38.484
were you with someone
that night?

15:41.482 --> 15:43.735
No.

15:43.901 --> 15:45.448
No?

15:45.611 --> 15:47.454
How did you get across town?

15:47.613 --> 15:49.411
Walk.

15:49.574 --> 15:51.076
Alone?

15:51.242 --> 15:52.243
Please.

15:52.410 --> 15:53.787
Okay.

15:53.953 --> 15:57.583
Yes.

15:57.748 --> 16:00.592
Liam, can you remember what
happened in the kitchen?

16:02.670 --> 16:06.766
Onions.

16:08.718 --> 16:10.311
