19:58.823 --> 20:01.121
Oh, my baby, come here. Here.

20:01.283 --> 20:03.377
You're my baby.

20:03.536 --> 20:05.163
I'm sorry.

20:07.123 --> 20:08.545
I am so sorry.

20:11.794 --> 20:15.094
Oh, Carrie,
I'm so sorry.

20:15.256 --> 20:17.099
Everything I've done,
I'm so sorry.

20:17.258 --> 20:18.510
I'm sorry.

20:18.676 --> 20:21.930
You're my baby.
I love you.

20:28.853 --> 20:31.106
I'm sorry.

20:32.648 --> 20:35.026
I'm really sorry.
I love you.

20:44.952 --> 20:47.125
I'm sorry.

20:49.582 --> 20:51.880
I'm sorry.

20:55.629 --> 20:57.427
Please.

21:10.853 --> 21:12.947
Come.

21:32.750 --> 21:35.594
Your leg still hurts?

21:35.753 --> 21:38.006
Yeah, a little bit.

21:38.172 --> 21:40.391
Listen, Trish.

21:42.718 --> 21:44.641
We have the murderer for sure.

21:44.804 --> 21:47.148
Sutter.

21:47.306 --> 21:49.229
The search
and rescue guy?

21:49.391 --> 21:51.189
No, not him.

21:51.352 --> 21:53.571
His son.

21:53.729 --> 21:55.151
His son?

21:55.314 --> 21:57.066
Yes, his little boy-- he did it.

21:58.400 --> 22:00.402
Little boy?

22:00.569 --> 22:02.446
Yes, he's ten years old.
He did it.

22:02.613 --> 22:04.490
A ten-year-old child?

22:04.657 --> 22:06.159
Yes.

22:06.325 --> 22:08.248
A child killed Charlie?
Yes, Trish.

22:08.410 --> 22:10.162
That's what
you're telling me now?!

22:21.632 --> 22:24.306
How do a mum and dad cope
with a thing like that?

22:24.468 --> 22:27.142
I don't know. I mean, how
does a little boy have...?

22:27.304 --> 22:28.305
Sorry, Markus.

22:30.683 --> 22:32.060
Have does he even
have the strength?

22:32.226 --> 22:35.196
Well, from experience,
I'll tell you.

22:35.354 --> 22:38.528
Children can be
surprisingly strong.

22:38.691 --> 22:40.864
A ten-year-old boy
having a tantrum...

22:41.026 --> 22:42.448
Tantrum?

22:42.611 --> 22:46.036
Well... struggling, you know.

22:48.617 --> 22:50.039
Hello, Henry.

22:50.202 --> 22:52.955
Morning, Shirley. Madness
has its own strength.

22:53.122 --> 22:55.750
There's an offer on
the Blue Swan vodka this week.

22:55.916 --> 22:57.088
I don't want it.

22:57.251 --> 22:58.377
Sorry. So,

22:58.544 --> 22:59.796
this child.

22:59.962 --> 23:01.305
Ten years old.

23:01.463 --> 23:02.840
It's a boy I know well.

23:03.007 --> 23:04.475
What about him?

23:04.633 --> 23:07.933
Well, it transpires
is the killer.

23:08.095 --> 23:10.063
I don't know.

23:10.222 --> 23:11.565
You run out of words,

23:11.724 --> 23:12.976
out of thoughts.

23:13.142 --> 23:14.940
What child?
I know.

23:15.102 --> 23:17.946
Beyond human
understanding, but

23:18.105 --> 23:19.357
that is what happened.

23:19.523 --> 23:21.867
Liam Sutter, ten years old.

23:22.026 --> 23:23.824
Hacked a grown man to death.

23:26.447 --> 23:29.667
I try to teach them that
life is a precious thing.

23:29.825 --> 23:32.874
A gift.

23:33.037 --> 23:34.254
Oh, hey.

23:34.413 --> 23:35.665
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

23:35.831 --> 23:37.959
Hey, what are you saying
about Liam Sutter?!

23:39.335 --> 23:42.509
What's he saying?!

24:02.650 --> 24:04.948
Frank.

24:09.740 --> 24:12.994
I understand that you were
telling me the truth

24:13.160 --> 24:15.413
about where the blood came from.

24:18.082 --> 24:20.756
We found corroborating evidence.

24:25.422 --> 24:27.641
Liam lost a fingernail,

24:27.800 --> 24:30.394
and it was

24:30.552 --> 24:32.850
inside Stoddart's body.

24:35.474 --> 24:37.522
Liam told us
what he did.

24:37.685 --> 24:39.858
He told us all
in front of his mother.

24:40.020 --> 24:41.317
Stop it.

24:41.480 --> 24:43.653
I am more sorry
than I know how to say.

24:43.816 --> 24:45.409
Frank.
Then stop it. Stop talking.

24:45.567 --> 24:46.864
You know...

24:47.027 --> 24:49.325
You know this
is all shit.

24:54.576 --> 24:56.874
Open this.

25:23.147 --> 25:26.321
Julia. I heard about your son.

25:26.483 --> 25:28.326
I'm s-so sorry.

25:28.485 --> 25:30.362
Is there anything
I can do to help?

25:32.406 --> 25:35.159
Take this.

25:35.325 --> 25:37.202
Can I help you?

25:39.163 --> 25:40.506
A drink.

25:40.664 --> 25:42.211
What?

25:42.374 --> 25:44.297
Have you got a drink?
A drink.

25:50.382 --> 25:52.259
Here.

26:08.108 --> 26:09.985
I've lost him.

26:33.092 --> 26:35.971
♪♪

27:02.830 --> 27:04.707
Jules.

27:06.625 --> 27:08.502
Jules.

27:28.856 --> 27:31.484
Questions of motive
don't even enter into it, do they?

27:31.650 --> 27:33.527
No, no.

27:33.694 --> 27:36.868
This is a profound psychosis.

27:37.030 --> 27:38.498
I mean, he takes
the chopping block

27:38.657 --> 27:40.910
and he smashes it down
on Stoddart's head.

27:41.076 --> 27:42.419
And then hacking

27:42.578 --> 27:45.206
and-and stabbing and...

27:45.372 --> 27:47.215
Relentless.

27:47.374 --> 27:50.878
I mean, I-inhuman savagery.

27:51.044 --> 27:52.887
From a ten-year-old kid.

27:53.046 --> 27:56.050
Where does that come from?
I mean, w-where?

27:56.216 --> 27:58.594
Well, this is not something
we're qualified to answer, Gene.

27:58.760 --> 28:00.979
I guess not.

28:01.138 --> 28:03.015
Okay.

28:05.184 --> 28:06.527
Pettigrew.

28:06.685 --> 28:07.777
Yeah, Pettigrew.

28:07.936 --> 28:09.404
They took the GPR scan

28:09.563 --> 28:11.531
but they left the folder.

28:11.690 --> 28:13.692
And on the folder
is written "Max 2.5."

28:13.859 --> 28:15.202
Yup.

28:15.360 --> 28:17.203
Nobody in technical
resources has

28:17.362 --> 28:20.081
any idea what has
a maximum value of 2.5.

28:21.658 --> 28:23.501
It's a name.

28:23.660 --> 28:25.003
Somebody's name

28:25.162 --> 28:27.836
in the research center.
That's what it is.

28:27.998 --> 28:29.875
Excellent.

28:31.543 --> 28:32.715
Are you okay?

28:32.878 --> 28:34.380
Yeah.

28:34.546 --> 28:36.890
You do know they put you
in the dead man's room?

28:37.049 --> 28:38.722
So?

28:38.884 --> 28:40.227
I was just thinking--

28:40.385 --> 28:42.934
get some candles,
close the curtains,

28:43.096 --> 28:44.939
have yourself a little séance.

28:45.098 --> 28:46.566
And ask Pettigrew

28:46.725 --> 28:49.194
what the fuck it was he found
before they killed him.

28:49.353 --> 28:51.230
Good-bye.

29:23.971 --> 29:25.848
Sheriff.

29:28.058 --> 29:30.481
Elena.

29:31.937 --> 29:34.440
You attacked Frank.

29:34.606 --> 29:37.485
No, no, I was trying to protect...
No, shut up.

29:37.651 --> 29:40.951
Shut up.
You attacked him.

29:41.113 --> 29:43.366
I'm brought in.
Questioned.

29:43.532 --> 29:45.876
I'm asked
about Pettigrew.

29:46.034 --> 29:47.911
Stop. Stop.
Just stop.

29:50.372 --> 29:52.921
I just came to say
one thing to you.

29:53.083 --> 29:55.927
Stay the fuck away from me.

29:58.880 --> 30:01.975
Forget it.

30:02.134 --> 30:04.808
You're bad.
You're a bad sheriff.

30:19.818 --> 30:23.197
Feed a fever, starve a cold. Mm?

30:23.363 --> 30:24.785
Mm.

30:24.948 --> 30:26.621
When I was a boy,

30:26.783 --> 30:30.538
my mother used to make
this soup for me, Shirley.

30:30.704 --> 30:32.957
Cream of chicken broth

30:33.123 --> 30:35.467
with little herb dumplings.

30:39.338 --> 30:41.181
I used to enjoy being ill.

30:41.340 --> 30:43.217
Just for the soup.

30:47.888 --> 30:49.731
Mmm.

30:49.890 --> 30:52.734
Utterly delicious.

30:52.893 --> 30:54.770
Sit up, honey.

30:59.149 --> 31:01.026
Sit up, please.

31:02.486 --> 31:04.909
Shirley?

31:06.531 --> 31:08.579
No, thank you.

31:08.742 --> 31:10.619
Markus, I can't.

31:17.417 --> 31:20.546
Well, we're gonna
have to do something

31:20.712 --> 31:23.591
before you fade away
to nothing at all.

31:39.981 --> 31:41.983
Yup?

31:42.150 --> 31:44.278
Is this room 2.5?

31:44.444 --> 31:46.287
Uh-huh.

31:46.446 --> 31:47.993
Max. Hey.

31:50.784 --> 31:53.287
You lost this.

31:54.913 --> 31:56.586
That's... That's not mine.
Look,

31:56.748 --> 31:59.467
before you go down
this sort of hopeless road of

31:59.626 --> 32:01.128
self-incrimination,
I should tell you

32:01.294 --> 32:03.012
that Pettigrew
made the scan

32:03.171 --> 32:04.764
that was in this folder.

32:04.923 --> 32:07.346
Now the scan is gone
and Pettigrew is dead

32:07.509 --> 32:09.807
and I think you know
who took it.

32:12.097 --> 32:13.724
And I would suggest
you tell me

32:13.890 --> 32:15.733
or you're probably
gonna wind up dead, too.

32:29.906 --> 32:31.749
Yuri Lubimov.

32:31.908 --> 32:34.832
Who is he and what does he do?

32:34.995 --> 32:38.295
He's the head of security
at the Russian mining town.

32:38.457 --> 32:41.051
Vukobejina.

32:41.209 --> 32:43.507
He left to go back there today.

32:43.670 --> 32:46.594
And are you frightened
of Mr. Lubimov?

32:50.594 --> 32:52.437
Yes, I am.

32:52.596 --> 32:55.440
I'll take care of him.

32:55.599 --> 32:57.476
Thank you, Max.

33:06.401 --> 33:08.745
You see, Tavrani, I think
all this tourist tat

33:08.904 --> 33:11.908
is a smoke screen
for what you really are.

33:12.073 --> 33:14.701
And what is it that I really am
in your eyes, my friend?

33:14.868 --> 33:17.246
You're a powerful man

33:17.412 --> 33:19.631
with powerful connections

33:19.789 --> 33:22.918
to the old world of
darkness and grudge.

33:23.084 --> 33:24.961
Say it.

33:27.005 --> 33:28.848
I think you are a shaman.

33:31.009 --> 33:34.559
Henry, I'm... I'm just
a stuffer of dead beasts.

33:34.721 --> 33:36.849
A peddler of tat.
A cigar store Indian.

33:40.310 --> 33:43.610
I can't fix your cancer,
Henry. I'm sorry.

33:43.772 --> 33:46.025
Not my cancer that
needs fixing.

33:46.191 --> 33:47.534
It's not?

33:47.692 --> 33:50.491
It's Liam Sutter.

33:50.654 --> 33:52.702
The little boy?

33:52.864 --> 33:56.619
I believe he needs very
powerful protection, Tavi.

33:56.785 --> 33:59.163
Something terrible
has happened.

33:59.329 --> 34:02.128
His young mother in a state
of shock and disintegration.

34:02.290 --> 34:04.793
Something is attacking

34:04.960 --> 34:07.554
them, I fucking know it.

34:07.712 --> 34:09.885
And I want you to build them

34:10.047 --> 34:11.971
one of those things
to protect them.

34:12.132 --> 34:13.635
What things?

34:13.802 --> 34:15.145
Oh, it's like a golem. Uh...

34:15.303 --> 34:16.725
You told me all about it once.

34:16.888 --> 34:18.264
You mean a tupilaq.

34:18.431 --> 34:19.603
That's it.

34:19.766 --> 34:21.518
A tupilaq.

34:21.685 --> 34:23.608
If I was a shaman,

34:23.770 --> 34:26.569
I would tell you that
there is no such thing anymore.

34:26.731 --> 34:28.199
If I was a shaman,

34:28.358 --> 34:30.702
I would tell you
that to complete a tupilaq

34:30.860 --> 34:32.862
according to all
the old rituals,

34:33.029 --> 34:35.031
the creature must be
finally baptized

34:35.197 --> 34:36.620
in the blood of a murderer.

34:36.783 --> 34:37.955
Do you follow me?

34:38.118 --> 34:39.916
Otherwise it will
have no power.

34:40.078 --> 34:42.877
Now... where would a shaman

34:43.039 --> 34:45.632
lay his hands on half a pint
of murderer's blood, hmm?

35:09.733 --> 35:11.610
May I join you?

35:19.034 --> 35:21.002
This is a 20-year-old

35:21.161 --> 35:24.256
Mossbank single malt whiskey.

35:24.414 --> 35:27.258
Distilled on the banks of...

35:27.417 --> 35:29.840
Dumfries and Galloway

35:30.003 --> 35:33.223
since 1788.

35:33.381 --> 35:35.224
And they have it here.

35:35.383 --> 35:37.260
In Fortitude.

35:39.179 --> 35:41.056
Incredible.

35:51.900 --> 35:53.777
<i>Sláinte.</i>

36:01.993 --> 36:03.836
I've ordered
the lutefisk.

36:03.995 --> 36:06.293
Good choice.

36:06.456 --> 36:08.584
Well, I thought I'm leaving
in a couple days time.

36:10.669 --> 36:14.299
Might as well find out the
truth about the lutefisk.

36:32.482 --> 36:35.281
Have you ever shot a man?

36:35.443 --> 36:36.615
Not with that.

36:39.114 --> 36:40.957
The lutefisk.

36:41.116 --> 36:42.993
Thank you.

36:47.997 --> 36:49.590
The truth about the lutefisk...

36:49.749 --> 36:51.626
Mm-hmm?

36:51.793 --> 36:53.670
...is you should never eat the lutefisk.

36:59.509 --> 37:01.386
Ugh.

37:19.195 --> 37:22.039
Liam.

37:22.198 --> 37:24.041
Baby

37:24.200 --> 37:26.077
Can you hear me?

37:30.248 --> 37:32.091
Can you hear me, Liam?

37:32.250 --> 37:34.127
Baby

37:44.179 --> 37:47.479
You don't know me.
My name's Elena.

37:49.017 --> 37:51.270
Um...

37:55.440 --> 37:57.693
It was my fault.

37:57.859 --> 38:00.282
What happened.

38:02.280 --> 38:03.873
Not your dad's fault.

38:04.032 --> 38:06.285
It was my fault.

38:11.539 --> 38:15.043
I'm so sorry, Liam.

38:18.296 --> 38:20.594
I'm so sorry.

38:27.931 --> 38:32.232
It was Christmas Day
when we landed in Scotland.

38:33.353 --> 38:35.526
Prestwick.

38:35.688 --> 38:38.362
And there were six
of us, all FBI,

38:38.525 --> 38:41.119
and they had a little coach
to take us to this town.

38:41.277 --> 38:44.156
And when we got to
the town, Lockerbie,

38:44.322 --> 38:47.201
a lot of the houses
were still burning.

38:47.367 --> 38:49.961
And we were each appointed
a local constable.

38:50.119 --> 38:52.963
The fella that was appointed
to me, his name was Stephen.

38:53.122 --> 38:56.296
And we were given radios
and maps and...

38:56.459 --> 39:01.590
a huge sack filled
with polythene body bags.

39:01.756 --> 39:07.479
So Stephen and I, we set
out across this moor.

39:07.637 --> 39:12.484
Every piece of anybody
we found...

39:12.642 --> 39:15.486
we picked up.

39:15.645 --> 39:17.693
I photographed it,

39:17.856 --> 39:20.700
and he bagged it.

39:20.859 --> 39:25.035
And we did that
all day, all night

39:25.196 --> 39:27.244
until our
torches ran out.

39:27.407 --> 39:29.501
And then we just sat
there in the dark,

39:29.659 --> 39:32.663
surrounded by 18...

39:32.829 --> 39:36.129
full body bags.

39:37.250 --> 39:40.094
But there was not a whole person

39:40.253 --> 39:42.506
in any one of them.

39:46.676 --> 39:49.395
And Stephen said,

39:49.554 --> 39:53.275
"Why could they not
have just stayed up there?

39:53.433 --> 39:57.404
Why did they have
to come down?"

39:57.562 --> 40:02.409
He said, "Why could they not
have just stayed up there?

40:02.567 --> 40:05.992
“Flying around the lovely world,

40:06.154 --> 40:08.407
forever."

40:18.374 --> 40:20.627
♪♪

40:43.399 --> 40:45.652
Shit.

41:13.805 --> 41:16.103
Fuck you, Ronnie.

41:49.090 --> 41:51.309
War stories.

41:53.594 --> 41:55.392
You show me
your scars...

41:56.514 --> 41:59.267
...I'll show you mine.

42:02.979 --> 42:05.027
This is about Pettigrew,
isn't it?

42:07.525 --> 42:09.823
I know
what you're doing.

42:11.612 --> 42:14.206
Psychology.

42:14.365 --> 42:17.414
You're using psychology.

42:30.298 --> 42:33.472
Billy Pettigrew
wasn't eaten by a bear.

42:33.634 --> 42:35.307
He was murdered.

42:35.470 --> 42:39.566
Now Professor Charlie Stoddart
has been murdered as well.

42:39.724 --> 42:42.318
The governor is responsible.

42:42.477 --> 42:45.947
Her sheriff killed them both.

43:18.971 --> 43:21.394
Someone called in,

43:21.557 --> 43:24.401
said they'd seen a man walking
out of town on his own

43:24.560 --> 43:26.233
along the coastline,

43:26.395 --> 43:28.489
without a rifle.

43:28.648 --> 43:30.867
Bear season.

43:31.025 --> 43:33.869
Time of year
when...

43:34.028 --> 43:36.076
the sea ice
is mostly gone

43:36.239 --> 43:39.083
and the bears are unable
to find seals

43:39.242 --> 43:41.119
so they're crazy with hunger.

43:43.621 --> 43:47.046
I drove slowly out of town
along the coast road

43:47.208 --> 43:49.427
looking for the missing man.

43:52.130 --> 43:54.633
After ten miles, I turned back

43:54.799 --> 43:57.427
because nobody could've got
that far in this temperature.

43:59.178 --> 44:02.227
On the way back,

44:02.390 --> 44:06.065
I saw a huge bear
down on the foreshore

44:06.227 --> 44:08.070
dragging its kill
across the-the rocks

44:08.229 --> 44:11.324
and the-the ice floes.

44:11.482 --> 44:14.782
I knew at once
what this was going to be.

44:16.237 --> 44:18.581
I pulled over,

44:18.739 --> 44:20.992
took my rifle,

44:21.159 --> 44:24.629
ran down onto the foreshore.

44:31.919 --> 44:34.513
The bear...

44:34.672 --> 44:37.425
was leaning over its kill.

44:37.592 --> 44:39.265
And...

44:39.427 --> 44:43.022
and in the split second
I took aim,

44:43.181 --> 44:46.685
I could see
that what it was tearing apart

44:46.851 --> 44:49.024
wasn't a seal.

44:49.187 --> 44:51.485
It was a man.

44:53.733 --> 44:56.486
The bear was disemboweling

44:56.652 --> 44:59.201
and eating Billy Pettigrew.

45:00.698 --> 45:02.871
And Pettigrew...

45:03.034 --> 45:05.787
was screaming.

45:05.953 --> 45:09.423
Inhuman screams.

45:12.668 --> 45:15.547
I shot Pettigrew
through the head.

45:38.110 --> 45:40.363
No witness.

45:42.323 --> 45:44.621
No motive.

45:46.035 --> 45:48.333
No crime.

45:53.626 --> 45:56.345
A mercy killing.

46:02.635 --> 46:04.888
Okay.

46:09.850 --> 46:12.148
Except...

46:14.272 --> 46:17.867
...I don't believe
a fucking word of it.

47:43.861 --> 47:46.831
♪♪

48:08.928 --> 48:10.100
Hey!

48:10.262 --> 48:11.935
Hey! Come here!

48:15.267 --> 48:17.520
Sorry, the door was open.

48:17.686 --> 48:19.984
When was this carpet changed?

48:22.191 --> 48:23.443
What?

48:23.609 --> 48:25.737
When was the carpet replaced?

48:25.903 --> 48:29.453
Why do you change
a carpet?

48:29.615 --> 48:32.459
Because there is
an immovable stain on it, right?

48:32.618 --> 48:35.667
Like red wine or something.

48:37.248 --> 48:40.502
But why do you change
the floorboards underneath?

48:40.668 --> 48:42.716
I-I don't know.

48:42.878 --> 48:44.721
I do.

48:44.880 --> 48:48.475
If the stain is blood.

48:48.634 --> 48:50.728
Pettigrew's blood.

48:55.641 --> 48:56.517
Hello, little bird.

48:56.684 --> 48:58.561
- My throat hurts.
<i>- Hello?</i>

48:58.727 --> 48:59.774
Let me know where
you're calling from.

48:59.937 --> 49:01.359
I don't know.

49:01.522 --> 49:03.524
Carrie? What the fuck?
What the fuck?

49:03.691 --> 49:04.943
<i>You'd tell me,
wouldn't you, if people</i>

49:05.109 --> 49:06.577
<i>were saying things that make me</i>

49:06.735 --> 49:07.827
look ridiculous?

49:07.987 --> 49:08.783
<i>Oh,</i>

49:08.946 --> 49:09.822
they're all in it.

49:09.989 --> 49:11.616
<i>They're all covering for Eric.</i>

49:11.782 --> 49:13.034
<i>Sheriff Anderssen, too?</i>

49:13.200 --> 49:14.668
I'm just an idea in your head.

49:14.827 --> 49:16.249
No.

